  "instructions": [
    "Peel and cut the yautia into 1-inch pieces and set aside.",
    "Heat the sesame oil in a large pan over medium heat.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for 1 minute, until fragrant.",
    "Add the chopped green onions and cook for an additional 2 minutes, until softened.",
    "Add the yautia, gochujang, soy sauce, sugar, salt, and black pepper to the pan, and stir to combine.",
    "Reduce heat to low and simmer for 10-12 minutes, or until the yautia is tender.",
    "Stir in the Korean chili flakes, if using.",
    "Add the chopped scallions and stir to combine.",
    "Serve hot in a traditional Korean brass bowl, garnished with additional green onions if desired."
  ],
